'''Sardar Gurbachan Singh''' ({{lang-pa|ਸਰਦਾਰ ਗੁਰਬਚਨ ਸਿੰਘ ਤਾਲਿਬ}} ([[Gurmukhi]]); 1911&ndash;1986) was a [[Sikh]] scholar, professor, and author. He was born in [[Moonak]], [[Sangrur district]]. He was a lecturer at the Sikh National College at [[Lahore]]. At the [[Banaras Hindu University]] he held the prestigious Guru Nanak Chair of Sikh Studies. He received the [[Padma Bhushan]] in 1985.<ref name="Padma Awards">{{cite web | url=http://mha.nic.in/sites/upload_files/mha/files/LST-PDAWD-2013.pdf | title=Padma Awards | publisher=Ministry of Home Affairs, Government of India | date=2015 | accessdate=July 21, 2015}}</ref> He received in 1985 the National fellowship by the [[Indian Council of Historical Research]], New Delhi.
